    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Triangular gable walls above the horizontal cornice of a classically treated building; also, triangular or roughly triangular elements, sometimes curved, or broken at the center, surmounting porticoes or openings. Common also on furniture, including as bonnet tops.</Note_Text>
